#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:97
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To play patience you need, as the name suggests, patience. For simple games, "
"where the way the game goes depends only upon how the cards fall, your "
"patience might be the only thing you need."
msgstr ""
"Kaardimängu Patience mängimiseks läheb vaja, nagu selle ingliskeelne nimigi "
"ütleb, kannatust. Lihtsamate mängude puhul, kus mängu käik sõltub ainult "
"sellest, kuidas kaardipakk on segatud, on kannatus ka ainus asi, mida sul "
"tõeliselt vaja läheb."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:103
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are also patience games where you must plan your strategy and think "
"ahead in order to win."
msgstr ""
"Kuid kannatust läheb vaja ka siis, kui kavatsed ellu viia oma võiduka "
"strateegia."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:108
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A theme common to all the games is the player must put the cards in a "
"special order &mdash; moving, turning and reordering them."
msgstr ""
"Kõigile mängudele on ühine see, et sul tuleb seada kaardid neid liigutades "
"ja ümber asetades kindlasse järjekorda."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:114
#, no-c-format
msgid "How to Play"
msgstr "Kuidas mängida"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid "Objective:"
msgstr "Eesmärk:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rearrange the cards by suit in as few moves as possible."
msgstr "korraldada kaardid võimalikult väheste käikudega mastide kaupa ümber."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:118
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As &kpatience; offers you a multiplicity of different solitaire games, there "
"is no straightforward how-to which could fit all of them. Therefore, it is "
"essential that you read each individual subsection of Game Rules, Strategies "
"and Tips section before you start playing a version you are not familiar "
"with."
msgstr ""
"&kpatience; pakub väga mitmesuguseid kaardimänge, mistõttu päris kõigile "
"ühtmoodi sobivat õpetust ei saagi koostada. Seepärast tasub uurida "
"mängureeglitest, strateegiast ja nõuannetest kõneleva osa vastavat "
"sektsiooni, enne kui asud mõne tundmatu mängu kallale."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:120
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Essentially there are two types of solitaire games – the ones that let you "
"arrange the cards by same color and the ones that let you arrange the cards "
"by alternating color. You can easily determine which game you are trying out "
"using trial-and-error method. Once you know which one you are dealing with "
"the rest is easy; keep arranging and rearranging the cards and collecting "
"the matching ones."
msgstr ""
"Põhimõtteliselt on solitaire'i tüüpi mänge kaht liiki: ühtedes tuleb kaardid "
"korraldada värvi järgi, teistes värve vaheldades. Seda, kumba liiki mänguga "
"on tegu, saab kindlaks teha kas või katse-eksituse meetodil. Kui see on "
"selge, on ka ülejäänu lihtne: korralda lihtsalt kaardid nii, et kokku "
"satuksid need, mis kokku sobivad."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"From the beginning, however, pay attention to your card stacks. Do not rush "
"to move individual cards around. See if it might be more useful elsewhere."
msgstr ""
"Hoia siiski algusest peale silm peal kaardipakil. Ära hakka uisapäisa "
"üksikuid kaarte siia-sinna tõstma, vaid uuri hoolikalt, kas kuskil on koht, "
"kuhu mõni kaart kindlasti peab sobima."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:124
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For additional help you can also take quick peeks onto the statusbar. Each "
"of the games has a built in solver which informs you whether the game you "
"are currently playing can be completed or not. If you see that solver could "
"not complete the current game, chances are you will not be able to do so as "
"well. At this point you can either restart the current game, or start a "
"completely new game."
msgstr ""
"Lisaks tasub silm peal hoida olekuribal. Kõigis mängudes on olemas "
"lahendaja, mis annab teada, kas parajasti mängitav mäng on võidetav või "
"mitte. Kui näed, et lahendaja ei suuda mängu edukalt lõpetada, on üpris "
"usutav, et ka sina seda ei suuda. Sel juhul oleks vahest mõttekam kas mäng "
"uuesti käivitada või alustada üldse uut mängu."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid "Note:"
msgstr "Märkus:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Playing solitaire games helps you to greatly improve your attention span and "
"enhance the ability to concentrate."
msgstr ""
"Selliste kaardimängude mängimine parandab tunduvalt tähelepanuvõimet ning "
"aitab paremini keskenduda."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:134
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game Rules, Strategies and Tips"
msgstr "Mängureeglid, strateegia ja nõuanded"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:137
#, no-c-format
msgid "General Rules"
msgstr "Üldised reeglid"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:138
#, no-c-format
msgid "suits"
msgstr "mastid"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:138
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A card game contains one or more card decks of 52 cards each. Each deck "
"contains the four suits:"
msgstr ""
"Iga mäng sisaldab vähemalt üht 52-kaardilist pakki. Igas pakis on neli masti:"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:144
#, no-c-format
msgid "Clubs"
msgstr "Risti"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:148
#, no-c-format
msgid "Spades"
msgstr "Poti"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:152
#, no-c-format
msgid "Hearts"
msgstr "Ärtu"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:155
#, no-c-format
msgid "Diamonds"
msgstr "Ruutu"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:159
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each of these suits contains the following card types: ace, two, three, "
"four, five, six, seven, eight, nine, ten, jack, queen, and king."
msgstr ""
"Igas mastis on järgmised kaardid: äss, kaks, kolm, neli, viis, kuus, seitse, "
"kaheksa, üheksa, kümme, soldat, emand ja kuningas."

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:160
#, no-c-format
msgid "family"
msgstr "mastirida"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:160
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This complete order of cards is called a family. There are real families and "
"alternating ones. The real families are all of one suit (&eg; Hearts). In "
"the alternating families the card color changes from one to another, between "
"a black color (Clubs and Spades) and a red color (Hearts and Diamonds)."
msgstr ""
"Kokku teeb see mastirea. Need jagunevad pärismastireaks ja pseudomastireaks. "
"Pärismastirida tähendab üht masti tervikuna (&eg; ruutu), pseudomastirida "
"aga seda, et mastireas vahelduvad värvid musta (risti ja poti) ning punase "
"(ärtu ja ruutu) vahel."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:161
#, no-c-format
msgid "If the family is not complete it is called a sequence."
msgstr "Kui rida ei ole täielik, nimetatakse seda osareaks."

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:164
#, no-c-format
msgid "The game field of &kpatience;"
msgstr "&kpatience;'i mänguväli"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:166
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are a number of features found in typical patience games. These are "
"described below."
msgstr ""
"Tüüpilises kaardimängus on vaid mõned elemendid, mida kirjeldame allpool."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:168
#, no-c-format
msgid "1. Talon"
msgstr "1. Algpakk"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:169
#, no-c-format
msgid "talon"
msgstr "algpakk"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:169
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At the beginning of each game all cards are mixed in the deck. In some games "
"not all cards are dealt out. The remaining cards are put down on the talon "
"(also called the stock). You can find this quite easily, since in most games "
"it is the only pile in which all cards are face down."
msgstr ""
"Iga mängu alguses on kaardid mänguväljal segamini. Kuid mitte igas mängus ei "
"jagata kõiki kaarte välja, vaid mõned on jäetud pakki. Selle leiab "
"mänguväljalt enamasti üsna lihtsalt üles, kuivõrd see on peaaegu kõigis "
"mängudes ainuke pakk väljal, mis on mängija poole seljaga."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid "2. Waste Pile"
msgstr "2. Heitepakk"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:173
#, no-c-format
msgid "waste pile"
msgstr "heitepakk"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:173
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Many games use a waste pile to hold cards taken from the talon. Typically "
"clicking on the talon will cause the topmost card to be flipped face up and "
"placed on the waste pile, at which point the card enters play."
msgstr ""
"Paljudes mängudes kasutatakse heitepakki, millesse lähevad algpakist võetud "
"kaardid. Tavaliselt põhjustab klõps algpakil selle pealmise kaardi "
"ümberkeeramise ning asetamise heitepakki, mille järel seda saab mängus "
"kasutada."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:176
#, no-c-format
msgid "3. Foundation"
msgstr "3. Lõpp-pakk"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:177
#, no-c-format
msgid "foundation"
msgstr "lõpp-pakk"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:177
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The foundation piles are where you want your cards to end up. Typically, "
#| "the game is one only once all cards have been moved to the foundation "
#| "piles in the correct order. The number of foundation piles and the "
#| "ordering required varies from game to game."
msgid ""
"The foundation piles are where you want your cards to end up. Typically, the "
"game is won only once all cards have been moved to the foundation piles in "
"the correct order. The number of foundation piles and the ordering required "
"varies from game to game."
msgstr ""
"Lõpp-pakid on koht, kuhu kaardid peavad viimaks jõudma. Reeglina saab mäng "
"läbi siis, kui kõik kaardid on korrektses järjekorras asetatud lõpp-"
"pakkidesse. Lõpp-pakkide arv ja kaartide vajalik järjekord erinevad mänguti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:178
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most games start with the foundation piles empty. Choosing the "
"<guimenuitem>Drop</guimenuitem> action from the menu or toolbar will cause "
"&kpatience; to scan through all the piles move as many cards to the "
"foundation piles as it can. If you have the <guimenuitem>Enabled Autodrop</"
"guimenuitem> setting activated, &kpatience; will attempt to perform a drop "
"whenever possible."
msgstr ""
"Enamikus mängudes on lõpp-pakid algul tühjad. Kui valida menüüst või "
"tööriistaribalt <guimenuitem>Paiguta</guimenuitem>, uurib &kpatience; kõigis "
"pakkides kõiki võimalusi ja liigutab lõpp-pakkidesse nii palju kaarte kui "
"võimalik. Kui sisse on lülitatud <guimenuitem>Automaatkäikude lubamine</"
"guimenuitem>, sooritab &kpatience; paigutamise alati, kui see on üldse "
"võimalik."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid "4. Playing Piles"
msgstr "4. Mängupakid"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:182
#, no-c-format
msgid "playing piles"
msgstr "mängupakid"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:182
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These piles are those where the actual reordering happens. The rules for "
"these piles vary a lot between games. Some show all cards on them, some do "
"not. Some allow only one card to be removed, some allow every card to be "
"removed, &etc;"
msgstr ""
"Need on pakid, kus tegelikult käib kaartide ümberjagamine. Milliseid "
"reegleid seejuures järgitakse, sõltub mängust. Mõnes on näha kõik kaardid, "
"mõnes ainult pealmine. Mõned lubavad eemaldada ainult pealmise kaardi, mõned "
"suvalise jne."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rules for Individual Games"
msgstr "Konkreetsete mängude reeglid"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:191
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Klondike</title>"
msgstr "<title>Klondike</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:193
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Klondike</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Klondike</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:193
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Klondike is the most famous patience &mdash; most likely because it comes "
"with a well-known operating system. It is played with one deck."
msgstr ""
"Klondike on usutavasti kuulsaim kaardimäng &mdash; eriti seepärast, et see "
"käib kaasas ühe sageli kasutatava operatsioonisüsteemiga. Seda mängitakse "
"ühe kaardipakiga."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:198
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The goal in Klondike is to put all cards, as real families, ascending on the "
"foundation. This gets easier once all cards are lying face up in the playing "
"piles."
msgstr ""
"Klondike'i eesmärk on seada kõik kaardid kasvavasse pärismastiritta. "
"Tavaliselt läheb see üsna edukalt niipea, kui kõik kaardid on jõudnud "
"mängupakkidesse."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:204
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The sequences on the playing piles have to be put there in descending order. "
"The cards should alternate in colors (red and black). You can move whole "
"sequences or parts of it, if the first card fits on another pile."
msgstr ""
"Osaread mängupakkides peavad olema kahanevad, kaardid võivad aga olla "
"vahelduva värviga (must punasel ja vastupidi). Liigutada saab terveid "
"osaridu või ka osa sellest, kui selle esimene kaart sobib mõne muu mängupaki "
"peale."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On a free pile you can put a king of any color, or a sequence starting with "
"a king."
msgstr ""
"Tühjaks jäänud mängupaki väljale saab asetada kuninga või kuningaga algava "
"osarea."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:215
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you click on the talon, one card from it will be moved to the waste "
"pile. You can move it to the playing piles or the foundation from there. If "
"the talon is empty, you can move the complete waste pile to the talon by "
"clicking on the empty talon."
msgstr ""
"Algpakil klõpsates liigutatakse üks kaart heitepakki, kust selle saab "
"liigutada mängu- või lõpp-pakki. Kui algpakk on tühjaks saanud, saab kogu "
"heitepaki uuesti algpakiks moondada, klõpsates tühjaks jäänud algpaki väljal."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:222
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can look through the cards on the talon as much as you like."
msgstr "Algpaki kaarte võib läbi lapata nii palju, kui süda lustib."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:228
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Grandfather</title>"
msgstr "<title>Vanaisa</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:230
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Grandfather</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Vanaisa</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:230
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This game was introduced to &Paul-Olav.Tvete;, the original developer of "
"&kpatience;, by his grandfather; it is named after this. No other patience "
"games are known to implement this patience game variant."
msgstr ""
"Seda mängu tutvustas &kpatience;'i esialgsele loojale &Paul-Olav.Tvete;le "
"tema vanaisa, millest tuleneb ka selle nimi. Teadaolevalt ei ole teisi "
"samasuguseid mänge olemas."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:235
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In Grandfather, one deck is dealt to seven playing piles. Some cards on each "
"pile are face down on the initial deal."
msgstr ""
"Vanaisas on üks kaardipakk jagatud seitsmele väljale, mõned kaardid on mängu "
"alguses seljaga."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:240
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The goal is to put all cards as real families ascending on the foundation "
"piles."
msgstr ""
"Eesmärk on seada kõik kaardid pärismastiridadena kasvavas järjekorras lõpp-"
"pakkidesse."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:244
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can move every card on every pile if it fits on another card, to build a "
"real sequence of descending order. For example, you can move the five of "
"spades on top of the six of spades, no matter how many cards on are on top "
"of the five of spades. Just the six of spades has to be on top of its pile."
msgstr ""
"Liigutada saab iga paki iga kaarti, kui see sobib mõne muu kaardiga, luues "
"kahaneva osarea. Nii saab asetada poti viie poti kuuele sõltumata sellest, "
"mitu kaarti poti viie peal asub. Kuid poti kuus peab olema oma paki pealmine "
"kaart."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:251
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On a free pile you can place a king (again no matter how many cards are on "
"top of it)."
msgstr ""
"Vabaks jäänud väljale võib asetada kuninga (taas ei ole oluline, kas selle "
"peal on kaarte ja kui palju neid on)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:256
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If there are no more possible moves, you can redeal the cards. A redeal "
"consists of picking up the cards from the playing piles (pile by pile, left "
"to right) and redealing them in the starting pattern (zigzagging rows of "
"face down cards forming a peak and then left to right rows of face up cards "
"on top). Note that the cards are <emphasis>not</emphasis> shuffled and that "
"cards on the foundation piles are left untouched. You may redeal no more "
"than twice in a single game."
msgstr ""
"Kui käike enam ei ole, võib kaardid ümber jagada. Ümberjagamine tähendab "
"kaartide võtmist mängupakkidest (pakk paki haaval vasakult paremale) ning "
"nende ümberjagamist algusmustri järgi (siksakiliselt varjatud kaartidega "
"ridades ja seejärel vasakult paremale avatud kaartidega ridades). Pane "
"tähele, et kaarte <emphasis>ei</emphasis> segata ning aluspakkide kaardid "
"jäetakse puutumata. Ühes mängus võib kaarte ümber jagada ainult kaks korda."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:265
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Even though the rules are simple and allow many moves, the game is still "
"hard to win. Despite this, or because of it, this game remains a joy to play."
msgstr ""
"Kuigi reeglid on päris lihtsad ja lubavad sooritada mitmekesiseid käike, ei "
"ole mängu võitmine ometi lihtne ja pakub suurt naudingut."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:272
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Aces Up</title>"
msgstr "<title>Ässad välja</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:274
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Aces Up</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Ässad välja</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This patience has simple rules, yet is hard to win. It is played with one "
"deck. The goal is to put all cards besides aces onto the foundation. There "
"should be an ace left on every playing pile afterwards."
msgstr ""
"Sellel mängul on äärmiselt lihtsad reeglid, kuid seda pole sugugi lihtne "
"võita. Seda mängitakse ühe kaardipakiga ning eesmärk on asetada kõik kaardid "
"lõpp-pakki, välja arvatud ässad, nii et lõpuks oleks igal mänguväljal üks "
"äss."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:280
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each top card that is of the same suit (&eg; spades) and has a lower value "
"than another top card (&eg; six of spades and four of spades) can be put on "
"the foundation by clicking on it."
msgstr ""
"Lõpp-pakki saab klõpsates asetada iga paki ülemist kaarti, mis on sama värvi "
"(&eg; poti) ning väiksema väärtusega kui teine pealmine kaart (&eg; poti "
"kuus ja poti neli)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:286
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you cannot move any more cards to the foundation, you can get a new card "
"for each playing pile by clicking on the talon."
msgstr ""
"Kui ühtegi kaarti ei saa enam lõpp-pakki liigutada, saab igale mänguväljale "
"asetada uue kaardi,  klõpsates algpakil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:291
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On a free pile you can move every other card on top of a pile. You should "
"use these moves to free piles. That way, new cards can be moved to the "
"foundation."
msgstr ""
"Vabaks jäänud väljale saab liigutada suvalise mängupaki pealmise kaardi. "
"Sellise liigutamisega saab vabastada alumisi kaarte, et neid oleks võimalik "
"lõpp-pakki asetada."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:296 index.docbook:384
#, no-c-format
msgid "The auto drop feature is disabled in this patience game."
msgstr "Automaatkäike selles mängus kasutada ei saa."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:303
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Freecell</title>"
msgstr "<title>Freecell</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:305
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Freecell</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Freecell</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:305
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Freecell is played with one card deck. You have four free cells in the top "
"left corner. In addition there are four foundation piles, and eight playing "
"piles below."
msgstr ""
"Freecelli mängitakse ühe kaardipakiga. Vasakul ülal on neli vaba välja. "
"Nende kõrval asub neli lõpp-pakivälja ning all kaheksa mänguvälja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:310
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The goal of the game is to have all cards as real families ascending on the "
"foundation. You can achieve this often if you know how to play: Freecell is "
"solvable at a rate of 99.9% approximately &mdash; of the first 32,000 deals "
"there is only one unsolvable (11,982 if you want to know)."
msgstr ""
"Mängu eesmärk on asetada kõik kaardid kasvavate pärismastiridadena lõpp-"
"pakkidesse. See läheb enamasti korda, kui sa tead, kuidas mängida, sest "
"Freecell on võidetav umbes 99,9% juhtudel (esimesest 32 000 variandist on "
"ainult üks mittevõidetav - 11 982 nimelt, kui see sind huvitab)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:317
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the playing piles you have to build descending sequences, where red and "
"black cards alternate. You can put any card in a free cell."
msgstr ""
"Mänguväljadel tuleb luua kahanevaid osaridu, kus punased ja mustad mastid "
"vahelduvad. Vabale väljale võib asetada suvalise kaardi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:322
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can only move one card that lays on top of a pile or a free cell. "
"Sequences can only be moved if you have enough free space (either free cells "
"or free playing piles) to place the cards."
msgstr ""
"Liigutada saab vaid üht kaarti, mis on mängupaki ülemine või asub vabal "
"väljal. Osaridu saab liigutada vaid siis, kui on piisavalt vaba ruumi (vabu "
"välju või vabu mänguvälju), kuhu asetada liigutatavaid kaarte."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:328
#, no-c-format
msgid "The maximum amount of cards you can move is calculated by:"
msgstr "Liigutatavate kaartide koguarv arvutatakse järgmiselt:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:332
#, no-c-format
msgid "(#{free cells} + 1) * 2<superscript>#{free piles}</superscript>"
msgstr ""
"({vabade väljade arv} + 1) * 2<superscript>{vabade mänguväljade arv}</"
"superscript>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:336 index.docbook:599 index.docbook:631
#, no-c-format
msgid "Variations:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:338
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Baker's Game</quote> is like <quote>Freecell</quote>, but the piles "
"are built down by suit."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:339
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Eight Off</quote> is like <quote>Freecell</quote>, but the piles are "
"built down by suit. You have 8 reserves and only kings can fill empty "
"spaces. Four reserves are filled at game start."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:340
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Forecell</quote> is like <quote>Freecell</quote>, but the reserves "
"are filled at game start, and only kings can fill empty spaces."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:341
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Seahaven Towers</quote> is like <quote>Freecell</quote>, but with 10 "
"piles which are built down by suit, and only kings can fill empty spaces. "
"Two reserves are filled at game start."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:344
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To solve this game it is recommended to grab the cards out of the playing "
"sequences in the same order they have to be put into the foundation (first "
"the aces, then the twos, &etc;)"
msgstr ""
"Mängu võitmiseks on soovitatav vabastada osaridade loomisel võimalikult "
"palju kaarte, mida saab kohe asetada lõpp-pakki (see tähendab esmalt ässad, "
"siis kahed &etc;)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:350
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You should try to keep as many free cells and/or playing piles empty, so you "
"can build sequences as long as possible."
msgstr ""
"Kui vähegi võimalik, tuleks hoida vabad väljad ja/või mänguväljad vabana, et "
"luua võimalikult pikki osaridu."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:358
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Mod3</title>"
msgstr "<title>Mod3</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:360
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Mod3</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Mod3</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:360
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Mod3 is played with two card decks. The goal is to put all cards on the top "
"three rows. In those you have to build sequences of the same color. In the "
"first row you have to create the sequence 2-5-8-J, in the second row the "
"sequence 3-6-9-Q, and in the third row the sequence 4-7-10-K. The suit of "
"the cards must be the same in each sequence, so you can only put a five of "
"hearts on top of a two of hearts."
msgstr ""
"Mod3 mängitakse kahe kaardipakiga. Eesmärk on seada kõik kaardid ülemisse "
"kolme ritta, kus tuleb luua ühest mastist osaread. Esimese rea osarida peab "
"olema järjestuses 2-5-8-S, teine 3-6-9-E ja kolmandas reas peavad osaread "
"olema 4-7-10-K. Mast peab igas osareas olema ühesugune, see tähendab, et "
"ärtu kahe peale sobib ainult ärtu viis."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:369
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The fourth row is both your waste pile and playing pile. On an empty slot "
"you can put any card from the first three rows, or one from the top of the "
"fourth row."
msgstr ""
"Neljas rida on korraga nii heitepakk kui mängupakk. Tühjale väljale võib "
"asetada suvalise kaardi ülemisest kolmest reast või mõne mitme kaardiga "
"neljanda rea paki ülemise kaardi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:374
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can put aces on the aces piles, on top of the talon. They are in the "
"game so you have a starting point for creating free slots."
msgstr ""
"Ässad saab panna ässade pakki algpaki kohal. Ässad osalevad mängus, pakkudes "
"hea võimaluse luua vabu välju."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:379
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you cannot move any more cards, you can get new cards on the fourth row "
"by clicking on the talon."
msgstr ""
"Kui kaarte enam liigutada ei saa, on võimalik lisada neljandasse ritta üks "
"kiht kaarte, klõpsates algpakil."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:390
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "<title>Mod3</title>"
msgid "<title>Normandy</title>"
msgstr "<title>Mod3</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:392
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "<primary>Mod3</primary>"
msgid "<primary>Normandy</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Mod3</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:392
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Gypsy is played with two card decks. The aim is to put all cards in real "
#| "families ascending on the foundation."
msgid ""
"Normandy is played with two card decks. The aim is to put all cards in real "
"families ascending on the foundation."
msgstr ""
"Mustlast mängitakse kahe kaardipakiga. Eesmärk on asetada kõik kaardid "
"kasvavatesse pärismastiridadesse."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:397
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The playing piles have to be descending, while red and black cards have to "
"alternate. You can only move sequences or single cards. On a free slot you "
"can put any card or sequence."
msgstr ""
"Mängupakkides peavad olema kahanevad read ning punased ja mustad peavad "
"vahelduma. Liigutada saab ainult osaridu või üksikuid kaarte. Vabale väljale "
"võib asetada suvalise kaardi või osarea."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:403
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you cannot move any more cards, you can click on the talon to get new "
"cards on each playing pile."
msgstr ""
"Kui enam ühtegi kaarti liigutada ei saa, katab klõps algpakil mänguvälja uue "
"kaardikihiga."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:407
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In using the <guibutton>Undo</guibutton> feature you can ease the game quite "
"a lot, as you have to take many decisions and some of them might turn out to "
"be wrong after you clicked the talon."
msgstr ""
"Käigu tagasivõtmise võimalust kasutades saab mängu tublisti lihtsamaks "
"muuta, sest mängus tuleb sul sageli valida mitme variandi vahel ning mõned "
"neist võivad algpakile klõpsamise järel päris valeks osutuda."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:413
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This game is also known under the name \"Gypsy\", but because this term is "
"considered derogatory and offensive by many, we have chosen to use the "
"alternative name \"Normandy\" instead."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:421
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Forty &amp; Eight</title>"
msgstr "<title>48</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:423
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Forty &amp; Eight</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>48</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:423
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Forty &amp; Eight is played with two card decks. The goal is to put all "
"cards as real families on the foundation."
msgstr ""
"48 mängitakse kahe kaardipakiga. Mängu eesmärk on asetada kõik kaardid "
"pärismastiridadena lõpp-pakki."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:428
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The playing piles have to be descending. Colors are important. You can only "
"put a five of hearts on a six of hearts, for example."
msgstr ""
"Mängupakid peavad olema kahanevad ning mastist tuleb kinni pidada. See "
"tähendab, et ärtu kuuele saab asetada ainult ärtu viit."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:433
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can only move one card on top of a pile. You can put any card in a free "
"slot."
msgstr ""
"Liigutada saab ainult paki ülemist kaarti. Vabale väljale võib asetada "
"suvalise kaardi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:437
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By clicking on the talon you can put a card on the waste pile; from there "
"you can put it on a playing pile or the foundation (&kpatience; will do this "
"for you). If the talon is empty you can put all cards on the waste pile back "
"on the talon. This works only once: after the second time the talon empties, "
"the game is over."
msgstr ""
"Algpakil klõpsates ilmub kaart heitepakki, kust selle saab asetada "
"mängupakki või lõpp-pakki (selle teeb &kpatience; sinu eest ära). Kui "
"algpakk on tühjaks saanud, saab heitepaki kaardid tagasi algpakiks moondada. "
"Seda saab aga vaid korra teha: kui algpakk saab teist korda läbi, on läbi ka "
"mäng."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:444
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This patience is difficult to solve. With some experience you can solve many "
"of the deals, especially if you use the <guibutton>Undo</guibutton> feature "
"from time to time to correct your decisions, and the decisions &kpatience; "
"makes in putting cards on the foundation."
msgstr ""
"Selle mängu võitmine ei ole kuigi kerge, kuid natuke harjutades suudad "
"kindlasti enamiku mänge võita, eriti kui kasutad aegajalt käigu "
"tagasivõtmise võimalust oma ekslike otsuste parandamiseks, samuti "
"&kpatience;'i otsuse parandamiseks asetada kaart või kaardid lõpp-pakki."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:453
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Simple Simon</title>"
msgstr "<title>Lihtsameelne Siim</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:455
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Simple Simon</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Lihtsameelne Siim</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:455
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Simple Simon is played with one card deck. The goal is to put all cards as "
"real families on the foundation."
msgstr ""
"Lihtsameelset Siimu mängitakse ühe kaardipakiga. Eesmärk on asetada kõik "
"kaardid pärismastiridadena lõpp-pakki."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:460
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the playing piles you can build sequences. In general you don't have to "
"care about the suits of the cards, but sequences can only be moved if they "
"are part of a real sequence. For example, you can move the six of spades if "
"the five of <emphasis>spades</emphasis> is on top of it, but may not move it "
"if the five of <emphasis>clubs</emphasis> is on top of it."
msgstr ""
"Mängupakkides saad luua osaridu. Üldiselt ei ole vaja masti pärast muret "
"tunda, kuid osaridu saab liigutada vaid siis, kui need on ühest mastist "
"(&eg; pakis teisena asetsevat poti kuut saab liigutada ainult siis, kui tema "
"peal on poti viis, aga mitte siis, kui selleks on näiteks ruutu viis)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:468
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The cards can only be moved to the foundation if all 13 cards of one family "
"lay on top of each other in the playing piles."
msgstr ""
"Kaarte saab lõpp-pakki liigutada alles siis, kui mastirea kõik 13 kaarti on "
"mängupakis ritta saanud."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:474
#, no-c-format
msgid "Suggestion"
msgstr "Soovitus"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:475
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You should try as soon as possible to move the cards to the correct piles, "
"to create free piles to place cards on temporarily, since you can put any "
"card on those."
msgstr ""
"Võiksid püüda võimalikult ruttu eemaldada kaardid parempoolsetelt vähema "
"kaartide arvuga mänguväljadelt, et saada vabu kohti, kuhu kaarte ridade "
"loomise ajal puhverdada."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:480
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With enough free room you can build families on free slots independently of "
"the color. If you have all cards in such families you can sort them by "
"color, so they can be moved to the foundation."
msgstr ""
"Kui ruumi on rohkem tekkinud, võib vabadel väljadel luua ridu mastile "
"vaatamata. Kui oled sellised read kokku saanud, on aeg sortida nad mastide "
"järgi, et neid oleks võimalik liigutada lõpp-pakki."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:489
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Yukon</title>"
msgstr "<title>Yukon</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:491
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Yukon</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Yukon</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:491
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Yukon is played with one card deck. The goal is to put all cards as real "
"families ascending on the foundation."
msgstr ""
"Yukonit mängitakse ühe kaardipakiga. Eesmärk on asetada kõik kaardid "
"kasvavate pärismastiridadena lõpp-pakki."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:496
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The sequences on the playing piles have to be descending with alternating "
"red and black cards. You can move every face up card no matter how many "
"cards are on top of it. So you can put a five of hearts on a six of spades "
"if that one is on top of its pile."
msgstr ""
"Osaread mängupakkides peavad olema kahanevad ning punase ja musta masti "
"vaheldusega. Liigutada saab iga kaarti sõltumata sellest, mitu kaarti tema "
"peal asetseb. Nii saab asetada ärtu viie poti kuuele, kui viimane on mõne "
"paki ülemine kaart."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:502
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In a free slot you can put a king of any color (again, no matter how many "
"cards are on top of it)."
msgstr ""
"Vabale väljale saab asetada suvalist masti kuninga (taas ei ole vahet, mitu "
"kaarti tema peal asetseb)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:509
#, no-c-format
msgid "Grandfather's Clock"
msgstr "Vanaisa kell"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:511
#, no-c-format
msgid "Grandfathers Clock"
msgstr "Vanaisa kell"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:511
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Grandfather's clock is a simple patience game. With some experience you "
"should be able to solve most deals. It is played with one card deck. The aim "
"is to put the cards as real ascending sequences on the foundation."
msgstr ""
"Vanaisa kell on lihtne kaardimäng ning pärast mõningast harjutamist peaksid "
"suutma enamiku mänge võita. Seda mängitakse ühe kaardipakiga ning eesmärk on "
"asetada kaardid kasvavate pärismastiridadena lõpp-pakki."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:517
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The foundation is on the right-hand side and consists of 12 piles that form "
"the shape of a clock. The nine is at 12 o'clock, the queen is at 3 o'clock, "
"the three is at 6 o'clock and the six is at 9 o'clock."
msgstr ""
"Lõpp-pakid asuvad paremal, koosnedes 12 kellakujuliselt seatud pakist. "
"Üheksa asub kela 12, emand kella 3, kolm kella 6 ja kuus kella 9 juures."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:523
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are 8 playing piles beside the clock and on each are 5 cards. On the "
"playing piles you can build descending sequences. The color of the cards is "
"not important. You can only move one card at a time."
msgstr ""
"Kella kõrval on kaheksa mängupakki, igas viis kaarti. Mängupakis saab luua "
"kahanevaid osaridu ilma mastile vaatamata. Korraga saab liigutada vaid üht "
"kaarti."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:532
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Golf</title>"
msgstr "<title>Golf</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:534
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Golf</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Golf</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:534
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Golf is played with one card deck. The goal of Golf is to move all the cards "
"on the tableau to the foundation."
msgstr ""
"Golfi mängitakse ühe kaardipakiga. Eesmärk on liigutada kõik kaardid lõpp-"
"pakki."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:537
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The layout of golf solitaire is straightforward. At the beginning of the "
"game you will see the tableau. On it are seven columns each containing five "
"cards. The talon and the foundation are below."
msgstr ""
"Golfi mänguväli on päris lihtne. Mängu alguses näed ülal seitset kaardirida, "
"igas viis kaarti. All asuvad algpakk ja lõpp-pakk."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:541
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Playing golf solitaire is simple, but requires strategy to win. The cards at "
"the base of each column on the tableau are available for play. Available "
"cards are built upon the top foundation card in ascending or descending "
"sequence regardless of suit. If there are no moves available a card may be "
"dealt from the talon to the foundation. The game is over when all the cards "
"in the talon have been dealt and there are no more possible moves."
msgstr ""
"Golfi mängimine pole keeruline, aga nõuab kindlasti korralikku strateegiat. "
"Liigutada saab kõiki mängupakkide pealmisi kaarte. Need tuleb asetada lõpp-"
"paki pealmisele kaardile alanevas või ülenevas järjekorras, kusjuures mast "
"ei ole oluline. Kui ühtegi kaarti enam lõpp-pakki viia ei saa, saab klõpsuga "
"algpakile lisada sinna uue kaardi. Mäng saab läbi, kui kõik algpaki kaardid "
"on välja jagatud ja ühtki käiku enam pole."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:550
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Spider</title>"
msgstr "<title>Ämblik</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:552
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Spider</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Ämblik</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:552
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Spider is played with two card decks. The cards are dealt out into 10 "
"playing piles, 4 of 6 cards and 6 of 5 cards each. This leaves 50 cards that "
"can be dealt out 10 at a time, one on each playing pile."
msgstr ""
"Ämblikku mängitakse kahe kaardipakiga. Kaardid on jaotatud kümnesse "
"mängupakki, millest neljas on 6 ja kuues 5 kaarti. See jätab järgi 50 "
"kaarti, mida saab kümnekaupa välja jagada, nii et iga jagamisega lisandub "
"igale mängupakile üks kaart."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:558
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the playing piles, a card can be placed on another card of any suit and "
"of one higher value. A sequence of descending cards of the same suit may be "
"moved from one playing pile to another."
msgstr ""
"Mänguväljadel saab kaarti seada mis tahes mastist, aga väärtuselt ühe võrra "
"suurema kaardi peale. Ühest mastist alanevat osarida võib ühest mängupakist "
"teise liigutada."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:564
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The goal of spider is to put all cards as real families descending from "
"Kings anywhere in the playing piles. When such a family is built in a "
"playing pile, it is removed to the lower-left corner of the window."
msgstr ""
"Ämbliku eesmärk on seada kõik kaardid kuningast algavate alanevate "
"pärismastiridadena mängupakkidesse. Kui selline mastirida valmis saab, "
"eemaldatakse see akna alumisse vasakusse nurka."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:570
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The different levels determine how many suits are dealt - Easy uses 1 suit, "
"Medium uses 2 suits, and Hard uses all 4 suits. The game is fairly easy to "
"win at Easy level, and very difficult to win at Hard level."
msgstr ""
"Mängul on vastavalt sellele, mitu masti välja jagatakse, erinevad tasemed: "
"lihtsal tasemel kasutatakse üht masti, keskmisel tasemel kaht ja raskel "
"tasemel kõiki nelja. Lihtsal tasemel on võitmine suhteliselt hõlpus, raskel "
"tasemel, nojah, seal peab ikka päris tugevasti pingutama ja ka siis ei "
"pruugi välja tulla :-)"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:579
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "<title>Yukon</title>"
msgid "<title>Baker's Dozen</title>"
msgstr "<title>Yukon</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:581
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "<primary>Yukon</primary>"
msgid "<primary>Baker's Dozen</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Yukon</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:581
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Baker's Dozen is played with one card deck. The game's name originates from "
"the 13 columns in the game, the number in a baker's dozen. The cards are "
"dealt into columns of four on the tableau, resulting in 13 columns. Any king "
"that is in the top or middle of each column must be placed on the bottom "
"before the game starts. Two kings that are mixed into one column are placed "
"on the bottom without changing their order."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:590
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The object of the game is to build all the cards onto the four foundations "
"by suit, each from ace to king"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:594 index.docbook:626
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "In the playing piles you have to build descending sequences, where red "
#| "and black cards alternate. You can put any card in a free cell."
msgid ""
"In the playing piles you have to build descending sequences, regardless of "
"suit. You can only move one card that lays on top of a pile."
msgstr ""
"Mänguväljadel tuleb luua kahanevaid osaridu, kus punased ja mustad mastid "
"vahelduvad. Vabale väljale võib asetada suvalise kaardi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:601
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In <quote>Spanish Patience</quote>, any card can fill empty tableau spaces. "
"(In some sources, the foundations are built up regardless of suit)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:602
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Castles in Spain</quote> is akin to <quote>Spanish Patience</quote>, "
"but the cards in the tableau are built down by alternate color. In some "
"variations, the tableau is dealt face-down aside from the top cards of each "
"column."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:603
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Portuguese Solitaire</quote> is halfway between <quote>Baker's Dozen</"
"quote> and <quote>Spanish Patience</quote> because empty columns can only be "
"filled with Kings."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:606
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "To solve this game it is recommended to grab the cards out of the playing "
#| "sequences in the same order they have to be put into the foundation "
#| "(first the aces, then the twos, &etc;)"
msgid ""
"To solve this game it is recommended to grab the cards out of the playing "
"sequences in the same order they have to be put into the foundation (first "
"the aces, then the twos, &etc;) Typically, you want to avoid emptying a "
"column until the last card is ready to be moved to a foundation."
msgstr ""
"Mängu võitmiseks on soovitatav vabastada osaridade loomisel võimalikult "
"palju kaarte, mida saab kohe asetada lõpp-pakki (see tähendab esmalt ässad, "
"siis kahed &etc;)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:616
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "<title>Golf</title>"
msgid "<title>Castle</title>"
msgstr "<title>Golf</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:618
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "<primary>Golf</primary>"
msgid "<primary>Castle</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Golf</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:618
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Castle is a family of patience or solitaire card games typically played with "
"a deck of 52 playing cards. It is sometimes described as \"Freecell without "
"cells\" because its game play is similar but without extra empty spaces to "
"maneuver in most variations."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:622
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The object of the game is to build all the cards onto the four foundations "
"by suit, each from ace to king."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:633
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Beleaguered Castle</quote>. Aces are dealt to the foundations. Any "
"card can fill empty spaces."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:634
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Citadel</quote> is like <quote>Beleaguered Castle</quote>, but "
"matching cards are moved to the foundation during the deal, leaving uneven "
"piles."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:635
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Exiled Kings</quote> is like <quote>Citadel</quote>, but only kings "
"can fill empty spaces."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:636
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Siegecraft</quote> is like <quote>Beleaguered Castle</quote>, but "
"with one free cell."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:637
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Streets and Alleys</quote> is like <quote>Beleaguered Castle</quote>, "
"but aces are included in shuffling."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:638
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Stronghold</quote> is like <quote>Streets and Alleys</quote>, but "
"with one free cell."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:641
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To solve this game it is recommended to build evenly on the foundations. Try "
"to create empty piles which can be used to facilitate longer moves to free "
"up buried cards."
msgstr ""

